 BY MAYOWA SAMUEL The All Progressives Congress has appointed Lagos State Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, to lead the 86-member campaign council for the Osun governorship election scheduled for July 16. In a notice on Tuesday, the ruling party’s national chairman, Abdullahi Adamu and national secretary, Iyiola Omisore, said the campaign council will be inaugurated at the party’s national secretariat on Thursday, June 23. “The inauguration of the All Progressives Congress (APC) National Campaign Council for the Osun State Governorship Election will be held on Thursday, 23rd of June, 2022 by 2:00pm at the APC National Headquarters, Abuja,” the notice read. According to the notice, Abdullahi Ganduje, governor of Kano; and Abubakar Sani Bello, governor of Niger, will serve as co-chairman and deputy chairman, on the council. Other governors — Kayode Fayemi, Atiku Bagudu, Nasir el-Rufai, Babagana Zulum, Hope Uzodimma and Bello Matawalle are among the 21 vice-chairmen appointed to the council by the party. Other members of the council include Babatunde Fashola, minister of works and housing; Sunday Dare, minister of youth and sport; and Gbemisola Saraki, minister of state for transportation. Osun State Governor, Gboyega Oyetola, is seeking another term in office, against Ademola Adeleke of the Peoples Democratic Party. The is the second time Adeleke, a former senator, will be seeking to become governor of the state. 